the fortified city? who will guide me as far as Idumea?","searchKeywords":["who","will","lead","into","the","fortified","city","guide","far","idumea"]},{"verseId":"brenton_psalms_59_12","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":24,"bookName":"Psalms","bookAbbrev":"psalms","chapter":59,"verse":12,"text":"Wilt not thou, O God, who hast cast us off? and wilt not thou, O God, go forth with our forces?","searchKeywords":["wilt","not","thou","god","who","hast","cast","off","and","forth","with","our","forces"]},{"verseId":"brenton_psalms_59_13","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":24,"bookName":"Psalms","bookAbbrev":"psalms","chapter":59,"verse":13,"text":"Give us help from trouble: for vain is the deliverance of man.","searchKeywords":["give","help","from","trouble","for","vain","the","deliverance","man"]},{"verseId":"brenton_psalms_59_14","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":24,"bookName":"Psalms","bookAbbrev":"psalms","chapter":59,"verse":14,"text":"In God will we do valiantly; and he shall bring to nought them that harass us.","searchKeywords":["god","will","valiantly","and","shall","bring","nought","them","that","harass"]}]